				\begin{document}$${T}_{0}={B}_{0}^{2}/{n}_{0}$$\end{document}). The plasma expansion velocity achieves a maximum of 1.5 V0 when the plasma is freely expanding, and then oscillates around V0 until the end of the simulations. The particle creation operator sustains a constant target density (ntarg = 2n0), mimicking the reservoir of the solid-density target. Particles are added at a specified cold target temperature (1 × 10−4 T0). The magnitude of the self-generated magnetic field is of the order of 0.25 B0.
